21 insurance established under existing law. (NRS 680A.080, 681A.010-681A.080)
22 Among the various kinds of insurance established under existing law is casualty
23 insurance, which existing law defines to include vehicle insurance, liability
24 insurance, workers’ compensation and employer’s liability insurance and various
25 other particular types of casualty insurance. (NRS 681A.020) Section 2 of this bill
26 expands the definition of casualty insurance to include legal expenses insurance,
27 which, under section 2, means insurance against any liability of a person or entity
28 for the costs of any specific legal services or specific legal expenses and which
29 pays or reimburses the person for the costs of the services or expenses. Section 2
30 excludes certain arrangements for prepaid legal services from the definition of legal
31 expenses insurance. As such, under section 2, legal expenses insurance is included
32 among the various types of insurance that a casualty insurer may be authorized to
33 transact and subject to any applicable provision of existing law governing casualty
34 insurance.
